{{See|At}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English < Old English '''[[æt]]''' < Proto-Germanic '''*at''', '''*az''' < Proto-Indo-European '''[[*ad-]]''' (to, near, at).

===Pronunciation===
* [[AHD]] ăt
* [[IPA]] [æt], reduced form [ət]
* [[SAMPA]] <tt>[{t]</tt>
*{{audio|en-us-at.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-æt|Rhymes: -æt]]

===Preposition===
'''at'''

# indicating place
#: ''At that precise position.''
# indicating time
#: ''At six o'clock.''
# indicating a target
#: ''He threw a rock at me.''
# indicating state
#: ''Men at work.''

